      "description": "This Z32 Nissan 300ZX Twin Turbo is a mechanically sound example of 90s JDM engineering. The VG30DETT power plant pulls hard through the entire rev range with consistent boost pressure from the twin Garrett T25 turbochargers. Mated to a crisp 5-speed manual transmission, the drivetrain delivers power effectively through the factory limited-slip differential. Recent service includes a full timing belt kit, water pump replacement, and a pressure test of the dual-intercooler tract to ensure zero vacuum leaks. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with a well-maintained driver, the Super HICAS four-wheel steering remains responsive and the suspension bushings have been refreshed to maintain lateral stability. A perfect candidate for the enthusiast looking for a high-performance platform that is ready for the canyon roads.",
